TV presenter and entrepreneur Maps Maponyane, is very passionate about his philanthropic work and what better way to give back than through education? The multi talented media personality has partnered with Pearson Institute to award one lucky student a bursary worth R75 000. “As some of you may know, I’m passionate about youth, education and giving opportunity; so I’m excited to have partnered with Pearson Institute to set up a 'Maps Maponyane Bursary' to a deserving student, or prospective student out there, valued up to R75,000,” Maps wrote on Instagram. Follow the link on the Tweet to apply   